list.name: Earth
list.description: The Moon is Earth's only natural satellite. At about one-quarter the diameter of Earth (comparable to the width of Australia),[13] it is the largest natural satellite in the Solar System relative to the size of its planet,[f] and the fifth largest satellite in the Solar System overall (larger than any dwarf planet).
